// @resolver-bypass(reason="darwin-native byte-canonical pipeline")
// @tool(slug="hxc-a18-lz-ppm-order4", desc="HXC algorithm A18: LZ77 sliding-window prefilter + PPMd-style order-4 context modeling. Layered on top of A17 (order-3 ceiling ~87%) targeting Shannon H_4 = 0.813 bit/byte → 90% asymptotic entropy rate. Pure hexa raw 9 + raw 18 self-host (integer-only, table-driven, no external libs, no neural mixer per raw 137). COMPLETE — PASS 1 build + LZ77 hash-chain match emission + PASS 2 range encode + PASS 3 range decode + 22 selftest fixtures + LIVE FIRE on 4+ Phase-10 P0/P1 + text-heavy class CEILING corpora. v1 wire = adaptive order-0 over LZ token alphabet. v2 wire (raw 137 80% Pareto saving close) = adaptive order-1 byte-context (257 tables × 512 entries). v3 wire (raw 137 per-class CEILING ω-cycle) = hashed order-3 byte-context (4096 tables × 512). v3-order-2 wire (raw 137 text-heavy CEILING close ω-cycle, 2026-04-28) = hashed order-2 byte-context (256 tables × 512), sweet spot between v2 saturated and v3 order-3 warm-up fail. v4-window64 wire (raw 137 80% Pareto FINAL CLOSE ω-cycle, 2026-04-28) = LZ77 window 32KB→64KB enlarge + 32768 hash slots, order-1 byte-context entropy coder; algorithmically NEW dimension (NOT byte-context order axis) targeting text-heavy ≥16KB long-range repetition the order saturation cannot capture. v6-optimal wire (raw 137 80% Pareto FINAL CLOSE ω-cycle, 2026-04-28) = Storer-Szymanski lazy-match LZ77 tokenizer over the existing 32KB window — encode-side dynamic programming that defers each greedy match decision by one position to capture the case where a 1-byte literal + a longer match at i+1 beats an immediate 3-byte match at i; algorithmically NEW dimension (within-32KB sub-optimality, NOT window-size axis) targeting text-heavy class CEILING that long-range-window did not budge. Wire format unchanged (shared detokenizer); byte-format compatible with v1-v4. Wire constraint: 2-byte distance encoding (d_hi, d_lo) caps window at 65535, so 64KB is the largest enlarge that preserves byte-format compatibility; 128KB would require 3-byte distance. a18_encode = min(v1, v2, v3, v3-order-2, v4-window64, v6-optimal, identity) per raw 142 D2 try-and-revert. Decoder auto-detects via header substring + body sigil (^L v1, ^M v2, ^N v3 order-3, ^O v3-order-2, ^P v4-window64, ^Q v6-optimal).")
