// (1982) lazy-match LZ77 tokenizer over the EXISTING 32KB window. Greedy
// match selection at position i is REVISED: if length L_{i+1} of the match
// at i+1 is strictly greater than L_i, emit a literal at i and re-evaluate
// at i+1. This is an encode-side optimization ONLY — wire format and
// detokenizer are unchanged (shared with v1/v2/v3/v3-o2/v4). Algorithmic
// novelty = within-32KB sub-optimality close (orthogonal to window axis):
// captures the cases where greedy LZ commits to a 3-byte match when a 1-byte
// literal + 6-byte match at i+1 would have been shorter. Sigil ^Q (vs ^L
// v1, ^M v2, ^N v3, ^O v3-o2, ^P v4-w64). Header v=lz-ppm-v6-optimal
// (NOT v5 — v5 reserved for future 128KB window 3-byte distance break).
// Per-class projected impact: text-heavy 79K n6 atlas v1=50% → v6=52-55%;
